what is css?
CSS means cascading style sheets , it adds styles to the web page.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How does CSS work under the hood?
The browser converts HTML CSS into DOM. DOM represents the document in the computer memory.
It combines the documents content with its style.Browser then displays the contents of the DOM.

Load HTML ----> Parse HTML---->Create DOM True -----> Display
                     |                                    |
                  Loads CSS---->Parse CSS------------------>   
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Differeny ways of using css in an application /?

Inline
Adding the style in the element itself using style attribute.
example :

<div style="width:200px;height:100px"></div>

Internal
Adding the CSS styles in style tag under header.
<head>
  <style>
    .app{
      width:100px;
      height:200px;
    }
  </styel>
</head>

External
write ur css in a separate file and add it to ur HTML page using the link tag.
Example : <link rel="url/styles.css"></link>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is diff between class selectors and id selectors?
Class selectors can be reused whereas id selectors are for single elements. 

class selector- represented by a .
id - rep by #

example : 

  .app{
    width:50px;
  }
  
   #appOne{
    width:50px;
  }
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is box model?
Box model describes visual formatting for an element. 
It has properties like :
1.Padding
2.Border
3.Margins
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is responsive web design?
This technique is used to display the web page perfectly on every screen size and device.
We dont have to create different web pages for each device.

Example: mobile,desktop, laptop, tablets.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are media queries ?
They are used for RWD.It applies different styles for diff devices.
Example: @media only screen and (max width: 600px){
//css styles
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are css positions ?

This specifies the type of positioning method used for an element.
There are totally 5 positions.
Position: fixed;
Position: static;
Position: absolute;
Position: sticky;
Position: relative;

Elements are then positioned using top, bottom, left and right properties.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are css spirits?
CSS spirits are used to reduce the loading time for a web page because it combines various small images into one image.
It reduces no. of Http requests and hence the loading time.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is reset or normalize CSS?
To have a generic default CSS property values we use this.To override the default settings 
of the browser and to have same default values. 
